From 63759d861fb26b3903586d00f1d37ffd945486ab Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Archana Suresh Patil <apatil@sandiego.edu>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 21:17:14 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [Model] Add MiniCPM-SALA (hybrid Lightning Attention + dense
 GQA)

Adds openbmb/MiniCPM-SALA, a ~9.5B 32-layer hybrid causal LM: 24 gated
linear ("lightning") attention layers reusing vLLM's in-tree MiniMax
linear-attention kernels + MambaBase state, and 8 GQA ("minicpm4") layers
using dense NoPE Attention. Lightning layers apply HF-exact RoPE and q/k
RMSNorm before an fp32 GLA recurrence; muP embedding/residual/logit
scalings match the released checkpoint.

The long-context InfLLM-V2 block-sparse backend (used at >= 8192 context)
is a planned follow-up PR; this PR is the dense model and is independently
useful.

Signed-off-by: Archana Suresh Patil <apatil@sandiego.edu>
